          "reason": "Dogfood: verified against current source tree"
        }
      ],
      "id": "REQ-0005",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Should",
      "rationale": "Humans occasionally need to hand-edit; repair is the explicit, audited escape hatch that keeps the integrity model honest.",
      "statement": "The system shall expose a repair subcommand that, when given --confirm-direct-edit, recomputes the integrity hash and rewrites the file.",
      "status": "Implemented",
      "tags": [
        "safety"
      ],
      "title": "Provide req repair to re-sign after intentional edits",
      "updated": "2026-05-17T07:14:36.503237500Z"
    },
    "REQ-0006": {
      "acceptance": [
        "Adding a requirement with statement 'The user clicks the button.' fails with a modal-verb error",
        "Adding the same requirement with 'The user shall click the button to submit the form' succeeds"
      ],
      "created": "2026-05-17T06:44:56.728504300Z",
      "history": [
        {
          "action": "created",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-05-17T06:44:56.728504700Z",
          "reason": null
        },
        {
          "action": "status draft -> implemented",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-05-17T07:14:36.650717100Z",
          "reason": "Dogfood: verified against current source tree"
        }
      ],
      "id": "REQ-0006",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Must",
      "rationale": "Normative modal verbs are the universal marker of a real requirement; their absence almost always means the text is descriptive rather than prescriptive.",
      "statement": "The system shall reject any requirement whose statement does not contain at least one of the modal verbs shall, must, should or will.",
      "status": "Implemented",
      "tags": [
        "validation"
      ],
      "title": "Enforce normative-modal-verb rule on statements",
      "updated": "2026-05-17T07:14:36.650716600Z"
    },
    "REQ-0007": {
      "acceptance": [
