          "reason": "Dogfood: verified against current source tree"
        }
      ],
      "id": "REQ-0026",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Should",
      "rationale": "Bidirectional traceability between requirements and code is most useful when it surfaces drift; a one-shot scan keeps the link cheap and grep-driven.",
      "statement": "The system shall scan a configurable source tree for occurrences of REQ-\\d{4} markers and shall report which requirements are referenced, which are orphaned, and which references point at unknown or obsolete IDs.",
      "status": "Implemented",
      "tags": [
        "integration",
        "traceability"
      ],
      "title": "Trace requirements to source with req coverage",
